    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-05-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-05-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="4"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d4">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">841.24/603½</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-05-16">May 16,
                            1941</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Cordell</hi>: I wish you would work out the over-all
                    arrangement between the United States and the British Government relative to the
                    consideration or considerations to be given us by the British in return for the
                    material provided under the Lend-Lease Act.<note n="11" xml:id="d4fn11">Approved
                        March 11, 1941; 55 Stat 31.</note>
                </p>
                <p>I should like to discuss it with you at an early opportunity because I think it
                    is important that we reach an agreement with the British at an early date.</p>
                <p>Although I presume the agreement will not provide primarily for a return to us of
                    cash, I think, nevertheless, you should consult with <pb facs="0014" n="6"
                        xml:id="pg_6"/> Secretary Morgenthau in regard to the broad provisions of
                    the agreement.</p>
                <p>Very sincerely yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Franklin</hi> D. <hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
